This is a program that shows how to use P5 and creating interaction between the user and the canvas. 

The four Modes are 

o Mode 1: Dynamic Background
o Mode 2: Animated Object
o Mode 3: Mouse Interaction
o Mode 4: Pattern Generation

mode 1 
- changes color based on the position of the mouse
- get map values for r, g, b based on mouse position
- red increases left to right
- green increases top to bottom 
- blue decreases top to bottom

mode 2 
- creates moving circle that bounces off on the edges
- changes color when you switch mode and get back to mode 2

mode 3
- it creates shapes when you press and drag the mouse on the canvas
- there is an option of cirlce or rectange
- the size of the shape change based on the mouse position

mode 4
- the whole canvas os filled with shape fillid with diffenet color.
- each circle have random fill color

To use this program you just have to run it and press 1,2,3,or 4 to get to the different modes
You can press 0 to get back to the menu